              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="allotments"></a>South Croydon Allotments Open Day Sat 12th August</h3>
                <p>SATURDAY 12th AUGUST 2017 from 9.30am – 1.30pm </p>
                <p>Come and visit our site and see how fresh veg and fruit are grown.</p>
                <p>We are a short walk from South Croydon Bus Garage, Sanderstead and Purley Oaks Stations.  Entrances from  Sanderstead Road at Broomhall Road junction, or next to the Business Park in Carlton Road (parking available).</p>
                <p>VEGETABLES,  FRUIT,  PRESERVES,  CAKES  AND  FLOWERS FOR SALE, BRIC A BRAC,  REFRESHMENTS, SAUSAGE SIZZLE,  SCARECROW  AND  PHOTO  COMPETITIONS.</p>
                <p>THIS YEAR WE ARE SUPPORTING THE ROYAL MARSDEN CANCER CHARITY (registered charity no. 1095197), and Action for Antenatal Results and Choices (ARC) (Registered Charity No 1148653) 
                </p>
              </td>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><%= link_to "South Croydon Allotments", "resource/allotments_open_day2017.pdf" %></h3>
              </td>
            </tr>

             <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="staycation"></a>Sanderstead Staycation, 29th, 30th and 31st August</h3>
                <p>Sanderstead Staycation, Aug 29th, 30th, 31st, from 10am each day. Why not come along and enjoy activities, games, discussions and crafts at All Saints' Church, Onslow Gardens, CR2 9AB. Activities are for people of all ages, 18 and over. You don't need to be drawing a pension! Places are going fast, so book early to avoid disappointment. Booking forms are available from the Parish Office in All Saints' Halls. To find out more contact Sandra Groombridge, email sandragroombridge@aol.com 
                </p>
              </td>
              <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/all_saints100.jpg", alt: "All Saints logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-parish.org.uk/all_saints" %>
              </td>
            </tr>


             <tr>
